During Ramadan, religious Muslims fast until sunset and often spend a good part of the day praying and reciting the Quran.The holiest month of the Islamic year is Ramadan. Fasting is an important part of Islam, and its benefits are thought to increase dramatically during Ramadan. Observant Muslims will refrain not only from eating during the day, but also smoking, swearing, and even drinking liquids. The word Ramadan comes from an Arabic word, ramaḍa, which means ""be hot."" Originally, Ramadan occurred at the hottest time of the year, but a calendar change resulted in Ramadan's rotation through the seasons.Ramadan: Ramadans   Ramadan

meaning: n.交响乐团；音乐爱好者；爱乐团体adj.交响乐团的
full_meaning: n.交响乐团；音乐爱好者；爱乐团体adj.交响乐团的；爱好音乐的           I have two tickets for the next performance by the philharmonic orchestra.我有两张爱乐乐团下一场演出的门票。      phil-, 爱, harmonic, 谐音, 和声, 词源同 harmony, 引申词义音乐.      adjective [ before noun ]uk/ˌfɪl.hɑːˈmɒn.ɪk/ us/ˌfɪl.hɑːrˈmɑː.nɪk/   used in the names of musical groups, especially orchestras（尤用于管弦乐队的名称中）爱乐的 the Vienna Philharmonic Orchestra.维也纳爱乐管弦乐团       The word philharmonic describes a group or organization that's dedicated to music. It's especially common as part of the name of large music ensembles like the New York Philharmonic or the Vienna Philharmonic Orchestra.Sometimes this word is used for orchestral music, so you could describe a symphony as a philharmonic piece. You're much more likely to find it in the names of symphony orchestras, though, from the Berlin Philharmonic Orchestra to the Los Angeles Philharmonic. The word was first used in English around 1913, from the Italian filarmonico, ""loving harmony,"" and its Greek roots philos, ""loving,"" and harmonika, ""harmony or music.""philharmonic: philharmonics   Philharmonic

meaning: n.马克思主义者adj.马克思主义的马克思主义的 ，马克思主义者 词性：形容词 , 名词            Last semester I took a class on Marxist economics.上个学期我选了马克思主义经济学的课程。      a.马克思主义的n.马克思主义者He is a Marxist.他是一位马克思主义者.            A Marxist is someone who strongly agrees with the political, economic, and philosophical ideas of Karl Marx and Friedrich Engels. If you're a Marxist, you're especially critical of capitalism.Marxists are particularly concerned with the struggles of lower and middle class workers, with the conflict between social classes, and with economic inequality. The ultimate goal of a Marxist is revolution that results in a classless society with fair distribution of goods. Karl Marx was a German philosopher, but the word was first coined in French, marxiste, in the late 1800s.Marxist: Marxists/Marxism: Marxisms, Marxist    Marxist
